# upsert a mobile pin
<%= partial 'documentation/partials/google_tag_manager_js' %>

Use the GET endpoint (/https://developer.qa.tax.service.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/api/service/mobile-pin/1.0/oas/page#tag/mobile-pin/operation/UpsertPin) to insert/update the hashed pin in mongo DB against a device Id


## Path parameters

Parameters must be entered in lowercase.

| Parameter   | Type         | Details                       |
| -- | -- | -- |
| nino    | string       | National Insurance Number of the user         |



## Query parameters

| Parameter| Type | Details|
| -- | -- | -- |
| journeyId   | string       | The journey ID of the user             |

[Link to Developer Hub](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk)

## Responses

Full details of successful and unsuccessful responses and their schema can be found in the [API reference](//api-documentation/docs/api/service/mobile-pin/1.0/oas/page#tag/mobile-pin/operation/UpsertPin) on the HMRC Developer Hub.

| Response code | Status | Details |
| -- | -- | -- | -- |
| 200 | Successful | Successful inserted/updated |
| 40 | Unsuccessful  | Bad Request |
